article_title: Lacey City Council approves conversion of Providence chemical dependency center
article_text:
The College Street center will be turned into a primary care medical clinic

Responding to public outcry, Mayor Andy Ryder asked several questions about proposed tree removal on the site

The new clinic is set to open in September 2016

article_metadata.news-keywords: Lacey, Lacey City Council, Providence Health & Services, Mayor Andy Ryder, Sarah Schelling, Providence primary care clinic, College Street clinic
article_metadata.description: Providence Health & Services can move forward on a plan to redevelop its chemical dependency center on College Street into a primary care medical clinic after Lacey City Council unanimously approved permits for the project Thursday night.
